==English==

===Etymology===
Established 1475-85 from {{LL.}} ''[[paradigma|paradīgma]]'', from {{Gr.}} [[παράδειγμα]] (''parádeigma'', [[pattern]]). See {{proto|Indo-European|deik-}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpær.ə.daɪm/}}
* {{audio|en-us-paradigm.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An example serving as a [[model]] or [[pattern]].
#* '''2000''', ''[[s:Estate of William F. Jenkins v. Paramount Pictures Corp.|Estate of William F. Jenkins v. Paramount Pictures Corp.]]''
#*: ''According to the Fourth Circuit, "Coca-Cola" is "the '''paradigm''' of a descriptive mark that has acquired secondary meaning."''
# {{context|linguistics}} A [[set]] of all [[form]]s which contain a common element, especially the set of all [[inflection]]al forms of a [[word]] or one of its grammatical category.
#* ''boy, boy’s, boys, boys’ is the '''paradigm''' of ''boy''.''
# A system of [[assumption]]s, [[concept]]s, [[value]]s, and [[practice]]s that constitutes a way of viewing [[reality]].

